    "millsfield:images_texts": [
      "A Transatlantic Clipper at Miami, Fla.",
      "One of the fleet of giant trans-Atlantic fly-\ning Clipper\nships which\nused Miami's tropi-\ncally located\nInterationl Air Terminal when\nNorthern\nharbors were ice-bound.\nThese are\nthe world's largest\nflying\nships,\nhaving\nwing\nspread of 152 feet and weigh (loaded}\n82,000 pounds; passenger capacity of 70; cover\nthe 4,000 miles to Europe in a little more than\na day.\nDL- 81— THOMAS R. WEST, MIAMI, FLA.\nGENUINE CURTEICH-CHICAGO \"C.T. ART-COLORTONE'' POST CARD (REG. U.S. PAT. OFF.)\nPOST CARD\nPLACE\nONE CENT\nSTAMP\nHERE\n0B-H248"
    ],
